s at the intimate realities of Filipinas, Chinese women, and U.S. men corresponding in hopes of finding a suitable marriage partner. Through the experiences of those engaged in pen pal relationships—their stories of love, romance, migration, and long-distance dating—this book conveys the richness and dignity of women's and men's choices without reducing these correspondents to calculating opportunists or naive romantics. Attentive to the structural, cultural, and personal factors that prompt women and men to seek marriage partners abroad, Romance on a Global Stage questions the dichotomies so frequently drawn between structure and agency, and between global and local levels of analysis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAsianszUnited States. 0aIntercountry marriagezUnited States. 0aInternational correspondencexSocial aspects. 0aInternational correspondencezUnited States. 0aMail order brideszUnited States. 0aMarriage brokeragezUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aamerican men.  aasian women.  achinese women.  acultural perspective.  aeastern european women.  aemail order spouses.  aethnographers.  afieldwork.  afilipinas.  aglobalization.  ainternet ethnography.  ainternet.  alatin american women.  alife partners.  along distance dating.  alove and romance.  amail order marriages.  amatching up.  amatchmaking.  amigration.  amisconceptions.  anonfiction.  aonline courtship.  apen pals.  astereotypes.  atransnational marriage.  avirtual ethnography.  awestern men.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052023705640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093722240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520937222423Coveruh